There is a weight that has no name. It arrives before language, before the day has given you anything to react to.

> We are good at naming the dramatic. We have almost no language for the chronic.

## What the body keeps

Not everything needs explanation to be real. The body knows this. Tension in the shoulders that has been there for two years. A jaw that is always slightly clenched.

### Physical signs of unspoken weight
- Persistent tension in the neck and shoulders
- Jaw clenching, especially during sleep
- Fatigue that sleep does not fix
- Difficulty taking a full, deep breath
- A low-grade sense of dread with no identifiable source

## Making space

Part of what we believe at Xolace is that the first step is not understanding — it is acknowledgment.

> "You do not need to know why you feel what you feel. You just need to let it be real."
